iacto is first found in the Paris ed. of 1507 (by Badius Ascensius). Haupt prints it in his small Vergil (1873), but it cannot be thought certain, owing to the doubt in 65 between deuictae, deuectae, deiectae. MSS. there are in favour of deuictae rather than deiectae (Peerlkamp) or deuel-tae : the latter is too weak a word for the utter rout of the giants. Retaining then in 65 deuictae of C (to which deiunctae of S also points), I incline to iacto in 64 as the easiest emendation of uicto.
